collection_readme.html:
Sensu Go Ansible Collection

Sensu Go Ansible Collection is a bundle of Ansible content that we can use to manage all aspects of Sensu Go. It contains Ansible roles for installing and configuring backends and agents. Collection also contains a wide selection of modules for runtime management of Sensu Go backend.

Collection is freely available on Ansible Galaxy. For Red Hat subscribers, this collection is also available on Automation Hub.

For user guides and references, please visit the documentation site.

description: A mapping of response codes to hooks which will be run by the agent when that code is returned.

description: Check command to run.

description: Schedule check requests using crontab syntax.

options.name: env_vars
description: A mapping of environment variable names and values to use with command execution.

options.name: handlers
description: List of handlers which receive check results.

options.name: high_flap_threshold
description: High flap threshold.

options.name: interval
description: Check request interval.

options.name: labels
description: Custom metadata fields that can be accessed within Sensu, as key/value pairs.

options.name: low_flap_threshold
description: Low flap threshold.

options.name: name
description: The Sensu object's name.

options.name: namespace
description: RBAC namespace to operate in. If this is not set the value of the SENSU_NAMESPACE environment variable will be used.

options.name: output_metric_format
description: Enable parsing of metrics in the specified format from this check's output.

options.name: output_metric_handlers
description: List of handlers which receive check results. I'm not sure why this exists.

options.name: proxy_entity_name
description: Entity name to associate this check with instead of the agent it ran on.

options.name: proxy_requests
description: Allows you to assign the check to run for multiple entities according to their entity_attributes.

suboptions.name: entity_attributes
description: List of attribute checks for determining which proxy entities this check should be scheduled against.

suboptions.name: splay
description: Enables or disables splaying of check request scheduling.

suboptions.name: splay_coverage
description: Percentage of the C(interval) over which to splay checks.

options.name: publish
description: Enables or disables scheduled publication of check requests.

options.name: round_robin
description: An array of environment variables to use with command execution.

options.name: runtime_assets
description: List of runtime assets required to run the check.

options.name: state
description: Target state of the Sensu object.

options.name: stdin
description: Enables writing of serialized JSON data to the check command's stdin.
Only usable with checks written specifically for Sensu Go.

options.name: subscriptions
description: List of subscriptions which receive check requests.
Required if I(state) is C(present).

options.name: timeout
description: Check execution timeout.

options.name: ttl
description: Amount of time after which a check result is considered stale.

doc_strings.examples:
- name: Check executing command every 30 seconds
  check:
    name: check
    command: check-cpu.sh -w 75 -c 90
    subscriptions:
      - checks
    interval: 30
    publish: yes

- name: Check executing command with cron scheduler
  check:
    name: check
    command: check-cpu.sh -w 75 -c 90
    subscriptions:
      - systems
    handlers:
      - slack
    cron: "* * * * *"
    publish: yes

- name: Ad-hoc scheduling
  check:
    name: check
    command: check-cpu.sh -w 75 -c 90
    subscriptions:
      - systems
    handlers:
      - slack
    interval: 60
    publish: no

- name: Report events under proxy entity name instead of agent entity
  check:
    name: check
    command: http_check.sh https://sensu.io
    subscriptions:
      - proxy
    handlers:
      - slack
    interval: 60
    proxy_entity_name: sensu-site
    round_robin: yes
    publish: yes

- name: Remove check
  check:
    name: my-check
    state: absent

description: Create, update or delete Sensu role.

options.name: auth
description: Authentication parameters. Can define each of them with ENV as well.

suboptions.name: api_key
description: The API key that should be used when authenticating. If this is not set, the value of the SENSU_API_KEY environment variable will be checked.
This replaces I(auth.user) and I(auth.password) parameters.
For more information about the API key, refer to the official Sensu documentation at U(https://docs.sensu.io/sensu-go/latest/guides/use-apikey-feature/).

suboptions.name: password
description: The Sensu user's password. If this is not set the value of the SENSU_PASSWORD environment variable will be checked.
This parameter is ignored if the I(auth.api_key) parameter is set.

suboptions.name: url
description: Location of the Sensu backend API. If this is not set the value of the SENSU_URL environment variable will be checked.

suboptions.name: user
description: The username to use for connecting to the Sensu API. If this is not set the value of the SENSU_USER environment variable will be checked.
This parameter is ignored if the I(auth.api_key) parameter is set.

options.name: name
description: The Sensu object's name.

options.name: rules
description: Rules that the cluster role applies.
Must be non-empty if I(state) is C(present).

suboptions.name: resource_names
description: Names of specific resources the rule has permission to access.
Note that for the C(create) verb, this argument will not be taken into account when enforcing RBAC, even if it is provided.

suboptions.name: resources
description: Types of resources the rule has permission to access.

suboptions.name: verbs
description: Permissions to be applied by the rule.

options.name: state
description: Target state of the Sensu object.

doc_strings.examples:
- name: Create a cluster role
  cluster_role:
    name: readonly
    rules:
      - verbs:
          - get
          - list
        resources:
          - checks
          - entities

- name: Delete a cluster role
  cluster_role:
    name: readonly
    state: absent
